 (296,'<h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Performing Arts</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">Billings boasts a vibrant performing arts scene, with its most popular venues centered around the historic downtown. The Alberta Bair Theater is the crown jewel of the city\''s performing arts realm, hosting a varied program of opera, live theater, musicals, concerts, dance, and comedy. Nearby, the Babcock Theater presents live performances alongside film screenings, lectures, and parties in a beautifully restored historic setting. The Carlin Events Center and NOVA are two other popular venues that boast a varied cultural program in downtown Billings. Further away, the Billings Studio Theater is a more intimate venue, featuring live theatrical performances by the local community theater. Billings is also home to the Billings Symphony Orchestra & Chorale, the only symphony orchestra that serves the cultural needs of the region. The symphony presents an annual season of performances, including the much-awaited Symphony in the Park and the annual Nutcracker ballet.</div><h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Live Music</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">The city\''s performing arts venues are complemented by an equally diverse set of options for live music and concerts. Housed within the old Billings bus station, the Pub Station is a popular choice for live music. The performance schedule spans a full spectrum of musical genres, featuring both local and touring bands. The bar also boasts over 30 beers on tap and a classic arcade for gamers. While the Alberta Bair and Babcock Theaters double up as concert halls, some of the city\''s largest concerts are hosted at the Rimrock Auto Arena at MetraPark. The arena has hosted the likes of Johnny Cash, Motley Crue, Elton John, Carrie Underwood and The Eagles.Pioneer Park and South Park are two of the Billings\'' top choices for outdoor concerts. While Pioneer Park hosts the annual Symphony in the Park, featuring the Billings Symphony Orchestra and Chorale, South Park is the venue of choice for the Magic City Blues - a two-day celebration of blues music.</div><h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Shopping</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">Downtown Billings is the city\''s main shopping hub, home to a diverse variety of stores to suit every taste. From trendy clothing boutiques stocked with the latest fashions, to antique and thrift stores selling vintage wares, downtown Billings is a paradise for fashion-conscious shoppers. Here, you will also find a variety of specialty stores that offer outdoor gear, fine jewelry, vinyl records, handcrafted gifts, original artwork, and much more.While downtown Billings is a hub of independent stores and boutiques, Rimrock Mall is home to the city\''s largest concentration of big-name brands. Browse through Montana\''s largest, the Dillard\''s department store, or shop at popular favorites like JCPenny, Victoria\''s Secret, H&M, and White House Black Market. For a quick snack, head to the food court where you will find a variety of quick-serve kiosks.</div><h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Museums and Galleries</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">Billings is a city that is proud of its heritage and boasts a colorful past. Explore the region\''s history at the Western Heritage Center, or experience the life of an affluent family at the turn of the century at the Moss Mansion. From a storied past rises the contemporary culture of modern-day Montana. Tour the Yellowstone Art Museum for a glimpse into the region\''s contemporary art scene. The largest museum of its kind in Montana, the Yellowstone Art Museum features varied temporary exhibitions alongside a vast permanent collection. Art enthusiasts will also find much to explore around downtown Billings where a majority of the city\''s art galleries thrive. Visit contemporary art galleries like Terakedis, Toucan, and Sandstone, or explore Art Alley and its ever-changing array of murals.</div><h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Outdoors</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">Billings and its surrounds are a haven for outdoors enthusiasts, with numerous trails, parks and natural attractions to explore both within city limits and nearby. The trails that riddle the Rimrocks of Billings are a great way to get acquainted with the city\''s mountainous landscape, before venturing further along the banks of the Yellowstone River, or the ski runs of Big Sky Resort. Unwind with a day on the water at Lake Elmo State Park, or enjoy a round of golf at the Hilands, Yegen, and Lake Hills golf clubs. The Billings Visitor Information Center is a fine place to begin your exploration of the Yellowstone River Valley and its many outdoor attractions. Other popular destinations nearby include the Yellowstone National Park, the Custer Gallatin National Forest, and Red Lodge. With so much to see and do, it is no wonder Billings is dubbed the \"Trailhead of Montana\".</div><h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Sports</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">Billings offers a variety of sports venues to cater to the city\''s many teams and sports clubs. While the Centennial Ice Arena is the home of the Billings Bulls Hockey Team, Dehler Park hosts the home games of Billings Mustangs Baseball Team. MetraPark, on the other hand, offers a more diverse program of events, with everything from sports, to concerts and trade fairs.</div><h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Festivals and Events</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">Home to a thriving cultural scene, Billings boasts a full schedule of events to be enjoyed across the year. From rodeo and concerts to community events, there\''s something for everyone. Popular annual events include the Downtown ArtWalks, SpringFest, and the Montana Renaissance Festival.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
 (297,'<h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Downtown</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">Downtown Billings is not only the core of the city\''s cultural sphere, but it is also here that the original rail town first bloomed. The city was established as a rail hub in 1882, with the foundation of the Northern Pacific Railroad Depot at a site that was previously known as Clark\''s Fork Bottom. Although no longer a rail hub, the historic depot still stands at its original site along Montana Avenue. Along this historic thoroughfare, lie reminders of the city\''s storied past in the form of historic edifices that have been transformed to suit contemporary functions. The old McCormick Hotel is now the McCormick Cafe, a thriving eatery that serves up some truly tasty fare, while the historic depot is now a popular events center. Here, you will also find the city\''s legendary high rises. While the First Interstate Center is the state\''s tallest building at a height of 272 feet (83 meters), the Doubletree by Hilton, previously known as the Crowne Plaza, is Montana\''s tallest hotel at a height of 256 feet (78 meters).From a diverse performing arts program at the Alberta Bair Theater, and exhibitions featuring contemporary artists at the Yellowstone Art Museum, to varied independent boutiques, and contemporary restaurants, downtown Billings is a treasure trove of delights. Art galleries, trendy boutiques, and local breweries complete the picture of a historic downtown that is firmly rooted in contemporary culture.</div><h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">Bottom West End Historic District</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">The Bottom West End Historic District is where you will find some of the city\''s oldest mansions. These stunning historic homes are lovely examples of the grand residential architectural styles favored by affluent families at the turn of the century.</div><h3 class=\"WorldGuide\">West End</h3><div class=\"WorldGuide\">The West End is one of the city\''s fastest growing neighborhoods. It is here that you will find Rimrock Mall, the premier shopping destination of the city of Billings, as well as the Yegen Golf Club.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
