 (336,'<div class=\"OverviewText\"><em>The Denver Post</em> once described Boulder as \"the little town nestled between the mountains and reality.\" Shadowed by the towering Flatirons and surrounded by more than 31,000 acres (12,545 hectares) of recreational open space and nature preserves, Boulder is 28 square miles (72.5 square kilometers) of outdoor heaven. Named after the mammoth rocks scattered across the terrain, Boulder brims with big city sophistication, college town intelligence, and environmental sensibilities.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
