 (364,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">Cutting dramatically through lush coastal plains, the Brisbane River coils like a snake around the cosmopolitan chic of Queensland\''s unique sub-tropical capital. Developed as a penal colony in 1824, the city spent years in the shadow of its southern neighbors. However, following the Commonwealth Games and Expo in the 1980s, investment skyrocketed, cementing Brisbane\''s future as a place of wealth, beauty, and excitement.Brisbane\''s architecture is a mix of new and old, featuring impressive Renaissance-style and timber <em>Queenslander</em> dwellings, which today share a berth with modern giants. Despite being close to the ocean, Brisbane is very much a river city, and the footpaths and waterways are a delightful way to explore the majestic metropolis.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
