 (393,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">Clearly defined in the popular tango — \"<em>Buenos Aires, la Reina de la Plata</em>\" — Buenos Aires is the Silver Queen. Emanating from the banks of the Río de la Plata are the sights and sounds of the city\''s indomitable culture and incomparable nightlife. Buenos Aires was born looking toward Europe, and as a result, it boasts a touch of Madrid and a touch of Paris. Some suggest that this stylistic mix even surpasses the originals. All that said, Buenos Aires is nothing if not its own destination, complete with tango districts, ubiquitous <em>colectivo</em> buses, magical coffeehouses, and above all, the dynamism of its proud inhabitants, the <em>Porteños</em>.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
