 (615,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">The heart of Cork is located on an island between two channels of the Lee River. Founded by a Viking marauders, Cork was once surrounded by medieval ramparts. Today, the erudite city flourishes as a thriving university town, and is deeply rooted in the tenets of academics, culture and arts. While the city is bisected into two islands by the river, the sections merge toward the city harbor, considered one of the largest in the world by navigational area.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
