 (871,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">Visitors and locals alike often refer to Halifax, and indeed all of Nova Scotia, as the \"best-kept secret\" in Canada. With one of the largest natural harbors in the world, Nova Scotia\''s capital is the biggest and most cosmopolitan city in Atlantic Canada\''s four provinces. Less than two hours by air from New York and Toronto, it is the halfway point between Europe and the west coast of North America.Halifax is a convenient city. Most points of interest, dining and entertainment establishments are within walking distance of major downtown hotels. The fresh breeze off the water make strolling a pleasure, and rooftop restaurants and bars are a good place to stop for a breather or to sample one of the city\''s locally brewed beers. It\''s an easygoing city where visitors can wander in comfort and safety until the wee hours.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
