 (1511,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">With a population of around 550,000, Oslo is one of the smallest capitals in Europe. The city\''s public transportation system is convenient and extensive, ranging from buses trams to trains and ferries, not including the subway system. This extensive network will take you all around town, into the wilderness, or out to one of the islands of the inner Oslofjord all in under 20 minutes.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
