 (1530,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">At a crossroads of ancient civilizations and the European frontier, Palermo is a complex of timeless, faded beauty, labyrinthine back alleys, sun-bright citrus gardens, and feisty street markets. It offers a mix of Norman castles of Moorish design, Byzantine art, and Baroque palaces. Visitors will find its best to begin their journey in the very walkable Centro Storico (Historic Center), where four ancient neighborhoods, also called <em>mandamenti</em>, meet, and then follow where the road leads from there.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
