 (1703,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">Rio is the second largest city in Brazil, after the megalopolis São Paulo. The many neighborhoods of Rio lie in three major zones: the <em>Centro</em>, <em>Sur </em>and <em>Norte </em>or Center, South, and North respectively. The affluent South boasts the famous Leblon and Ipanema beaches while the Center encompasses the historic Santa Teresa and Lapa neighborhoods. The majority of tourist attractions are shared between these two districts. The North, on the other hand, is more suburban in character with the Galeão airport as its linchpin.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
