 (1712,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">The subject of an endless number of historic plays and movies, the stories surrounding Rome have permeated the depths of Western culture. From The Vatican to the Colosseum, Rome\''s deep history and cultural significance is evidenced by every monument and palazzo. Seeing Rome as it is today, it may be hard to imagine that this sprawling metropolis began with a small settlement of shepherds and farmers near the Tiber River on the Palatine Hill, the same site where Augustus, the first Emperor, built his home. The old city occupied six other hills (Quirinal, Viminal, Esquiline, Caelian, Aventine and Capitoline), though the modern city extends far beyond those confines.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
