 (1760,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">Salzburg is located in the so-called Salzburg Basin, on the northern border of the Alps, surrounded by the Kapuzinerberg, the Mönchsberg and the Gaisberg mountains. Although there are official districts, not all of them are of interest when giving an overview of Salzburg. There are a few districts that have a distinct feel to them, but it is the city\''s historic Altstadt (Old Town) that deserves the most attention.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
