 (1955,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">St. Louis experienced a population boom during the late 1800s when German and Italian immigrants settled in large numbers. Thanks to the work of several visionary thinkers, the city became home to the first concrete stadium, Francis Field at Washington University; the first skyscraper, the Wainwright Building; and the first ice cream cone, served at the 1904 World\''s Fair, among other novel creations. A mix of Old World charm and modern life continues to be a hallmark of this vibrant Midwestern city, in which each neighborhood has its own history and unique character.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
