 (1984,'Birds rest by a pond in front of the State Opera House in Stuttgart.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
 (1985,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">The city and its name originate from a horse farm, <em>Stutengarten</em>, which was founded in 950 CE in the Nesenbach Valley. Formerly an agricultural region, it developed into a beautiful residential town, and later forged important industrial links. Daimler, Bosch and Porsche are just some of the famous names that have been associated with Stuttgart. Other than that, it is a wine-making area that is renowned for its verdant parks and gardens. Those who visit Stuttgart are often fascinated by how well the city\''s natural setting harmonizes with its historically significant role as an industrial powerhouse.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
