 (2504,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">Nestled in the shadow of five mountain ranges, this Western Montana city wears its natural beauty with pride. It is home to dozens of parks and gardens, as well as to the snow-capped peaks of Mount Jumbo. To add to its already dramatic terrain, the Clark Fork river cuts through several of the city\''s districts. Besides being a scenic stunner, the city is also the site of the University of Montana, the first state university. This lends a whole new facet to the city\''s personality, with the U District (University District) being billed as one of the hippest neighborhoods in town. Missoula has a storied architectural past too, with surviving examples from the 19th and 20th Centuries still lining city streets. With such a fascinating makeup and versatile milieu, the city is sectioned into varying districts and neighborhoods, each with its own distinct persona.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
