 (3017,'<div class=\"OverviewText\">Martha\''s Vineyard is bounded by Vineyard Sound, Nantucket Sound and the Atlantic Ocean. Martha\''s Vineyard is accessible only via boat or by air and has long been known as a summer retreat for the affluent under colonial rule. Today, the island encompasses quaint harbor towns, picturesque seascapes, and historic lighthouses. Just five miles (8.04 kilometers) south of Cape Cod, in the state of Massachusetts, this island is noted for its varied landscape and the individual character of its towns and residents.</div><br><div class=\"FodorsCopyright\">&copy; Cityseeker</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
